quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  44,17,"Certainly We tried the people of Pharaoh before them, when a noble apostle came to them"
  44,18,"[saying,] ‘Give over the servants of Allah to me; indeed I am a trusted apostle [sent] to you"
  44,19,Do not defy Allah. Indeed I bring you a manifest authority
  44,20,"I seek the protection of my Lord and your Lord, lest you should stone me"
  44,21,"And if you do not believe me, keep out of my way.’"
  44,22,"Then he invoked his Lord, [saying,] ‘These are indeed a guilty lot.’"
  44,23,"[Allah told him,] ‘Set out by night with My servants; for you will be pursued"
  44,24,Leave behind the sea unmoving; for they will be a drowned host.’
  44,25,How many gardens and springs did they leave behind
  44,26,Fields and splendid places
  44,27,and the affluence wherein they rejoiced
  44,28,So it was; and We bequeathed them to another people
  44,29,"So neither the sky wept for them, nor the earth; nor were they granted any respite"
  44,30,Certainly We delivered the Children of Israel from the humiliating torment
  44,31,"of Pharaoh. Indeed, he was a tyrant among the transgressors"
  44,32,Certainly We chose them knowingly above all the nations
  44,33,and We gave them some signs in which there was a manifest test
  44,34,These ones say
  44,35,"‘It will be only our first death, and we shall not be resurrected"
  44,36,"Bring our fathers back [to life], if you are truthful.’"
  44,37,"Are they better, or the people of Tubba‘, and those who were before them? We destroyed them; indeed, they were guilty"
  44,38,We did not create the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them for play
  44,39,We did not create them except with consummate wisdom; but most of them do not know
  44,40,Indeed the Day of Judgement is the tryst for them all
  44,41,"the day when a friend will not avail a friend in any way, nor will they be helped"
  44,42,"except for him on whom Allah has mercy. Indeed He is the All-mighty, the All-merciful"
  44,43,Indeed the tree of Zaqqum
  44,44,will be the food of the sinful
  44,45,Like molten copper it will boil in their bellies
  44,46,seething like boiling water
  44,47,"[The keepers of hell will be told,] ‘Seize him and drag him to the middle of hell"
  44,48,then pour over his head boiling water as punishment
  44,49,"[and tell them,] “Taste this! Indeed you are the [self-styled] mighty and noble"
  44,50,This is what you used to doubt!’
  44,51,Indeed the Godwary will be in a safe place
  44,52,amid gardens and springs
  44,53,"dressed in fine silk and brocade, sitting face to face"
  44,54,"So shall it be, and We shall wed them to black-eyed houris"
  44,55,"Secure [from any kind of harm,] there they will call for every kind of fruit [they wish]"
  44,56,"Other than the first death, they will not taste death therein, and He will save them from the punishment of hell"
  44,57,—a grace from your Lord. That is the great success
  44,58,"Indeed We have made it simple in your language, so that they may take admonition"
  44,59,"So wait! They [too] are waiting"
  45,1,"Ha, Meem"
  45,2,"The [gradual] sending down of the Book is from Allah, the All-mighty, All-wise"
  45,3,In the heavens and the earth there are indeed signs for the faithful
  45,4,"There are signs for people who have certainty in your own creation and in animals, He scatters abroad"
  45,5,"There are signs for people who exercise their reason in the alternation of night and day, in the provision that Allah sends down from the sky, with which He revives the earth after its death, and in the changing of the winds"
  45,6,These are the signs of Allah that We recite for you in truth. So what discourse will they believe after Allah and His signs
  45,7,Woe to every sinful liar
  45,8,"who hears the signs of Allah being recited to him, yet persists arrogantly as if he had not heard them. So inform him of a painful punishment"
  45,9,"Should he learn anything about Our signs, he takes them in derision. For such there is a humiliating punishment"
  45,10,"Ahead of them is hell, and neither what they have earned, nor what they had taken as guardians besides Allah will avail them in any way, and there is a great punishment for them"
  45,11,"This is [true] guidance, and there is a painful punishment due to defilement for those who defy the signs of their Lord"